   Center for Integration of Natural Disaster Information

   Earthquake

   The USGS Earthquake Hazards Program web site provides links to USGS web
   sites dedicated to earthquake information, including earthquake
   activity, research, products, and education.
   The USGS National Earthquake Information Center (NEIC)
   World Data Center for Seismology, Denver, Colorado
   Real-time earthquake information provided by USGS
    For information on earthquakes recorded during the previous 48 hours,
   call
   The USGS Earthquake Information Line
   (303) 273-8516
   The recording includes information on felt earthquakes within the
   United States as well as felt earthquakes throughout the world of
   magnitude 5.5 or greater. The recorded message is updated twice daily
   by the NEIC, and is available 24 hours a day.

